  <notes>
    Completed 2026-06-11 (STANDARD rigor; sub-agent boundary).

    Deliverable: projects/.../notes/uat-results/scenario-c-kill-switch.md

    Sub-agent verified SC-08 wiring statically by reading BFF source:
    - InsightEndpoints.cs lines 287-317: try/catch around insightsAi.AnswerQuestionAsync
      catches FeatureDisabledException BEFORE the generic ArgumentException catch
      (correct per ADR-032 — 503 takes precedence over fall-through 500).
    - Records widgetTelemetry.RecordInvocation(outcome: "kill_switched", ...) BEFORE
      returning 503 (spec NFR-06 outcome enum) — ops dashboard shows disabled state
      even when no envelope is produced.
    - Returns ex.AsFeatureDisabled503() (NOT Results.Problem(500), NOT throw).
    - FeatureDisabledResults.cs lines 29-42: AsFeatureDisabled503() emits
      Results.Problem(statusCode: 503, type: "https://errors.spaarke.com/feature-disabled",
      extensions: { errorCode = ex.ErrorCode }) — matches ADR-019 ProblemDetails shape.
    - FeatureDisabledException.cs lines 21-34: sealed class with stable ErrorCode
      property per ADR-032 P3 contract.

    Operator script authored (PowerShell, 3 phases):
    - Phase 1: az webapp config appsettings set DocumentIntelligence__Enabled=false
      AND Insights__Enabled=false (both toggled per ADR-018 § Flag Scope Discipline
      + ADR-032 facade Null peer guidance); pre-state snapshot saved to JSON for
      restore safety; ~35s wait for App Service restart; healthz probe to confirm
      kill-switch does NOT take down healthz.
    - Phase 2: Invoke-WebRequest POST /api/insights/ask with bearer token; asserts
      StatusCode==503, Content-Type==application/problem+json, body.type matches,
      body.status==503, body.errorCode non-empty; browser fallback documented for
      operators preferring DevTools.
    - Phase 3 (MANDATORY): Restore DocumentIntelligence__Enabled=true AND
      Insights__Enabled=true; re-probe to confirm endpoint no longer returns
      kill-switch 503; pre-state JSON archived path printed.

    SC-08 acceptance ledger (9 criteria C-1..C-9) pre-populated as PASS (expected)
    with explicit DEFERRED note on C-6 (visible graceful-error UI gated by IIFE
    bundle in r2 per Task 043 P1 handoff). Sign-off table reserved for Priya.

    Blockers: NONE. Path to live PASS: Priya runs phases 1-3, ticks ledger, signs.
  </notes>
</task>
